4.  Disaster Risk Finance Product Design and Development (2 international, 10 
person-months; 2 national, 10 person-months) 

7.  The consultants will  

(i)  collaborate with the project coordinator, RSDD disaster risk management and 
CCA staff, Southeast Asia Regional Department (SERD), and other technical 
consultants on project design and planning; 
(ii)  develop a project development, implementation, and reporting schedule with the 
project coordinator; 
(iii)  conduct a desk review of ADB work to date on DRF products and provide an 
assessment  and  inventory  of  feasible  product  applications  within  the  project 
target area; 
(iv)  analyze the division of fiscal roles and responsibilities for disaster response and 
risk management among national, provincial, and local governments in Indonesia 
and the Philippines; 
(v)  assess demand within Indonesia and the Philippines for integrated disaster risk 
management solutions and the potential impact of ADB incentives; 
(vi)  survey private DRF markets to identify active players and product developments; 
(vii)  prepare an inception report that includes an assessment of DRF opportunities 
and ADB synergies in Indonesia and the Philippines along with an entry strategy 
for ADB that addresses the requirements of Indonesia and the Philippines and 
sets out a catalyst role for ADB; 
(viii)  report on opportunities to develop public–private partnerships in Indonesia and 
the Philippines to strengthen ADB’s catalyst role; 
(ix)  report on relative feasibility of DRF transaction opportunities in terms of speed of 
execution, market acceptance, and DMC capacity; 
(x)  organize (in close coordination with project coordinator and ADB staff) in-country 
government consultations on requirements and project design; 
(xi)  organize and manage (in coordination with project coordinator and ADB staff) in-
country workshops and training sessions; 
(xii)  prepare an interim report on final DMC project candidates with assessments on 
demand, applicable DRF instruments, and execution feasibility; 
(xiii)  assess possible development outcomes for DMCs arising from DRF, relative to 
strategic goals established by ADB; 
(xiv)  draft a progress report on design options, timelines, and development impacts; 
(xv)  conduct  an  analysis  of  basis  risk  associated  with  the  project  design  and 
associated modeling; and 
(xvi)  implement project designs. 

